      <back>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>The tombstone was found in the southwestern part of the cemetery. The upper part of the stone is chisel dressed and badly weathered. The lower part of the stone is roughly picked. The author thinks that the use of common formula "Courage" and "no one is immortal" mark tombstones in this group as pre-Christian.</p>
         </div>
